%N A394249 Number of partitions of n into two 7-smooth numbers.
%C A394249 The two 7-smooth numbers can be equal.
%e A394249 a(7) = 3 because 7 has 3 ways to be written as two 7-smooth numbers: 7 = 6 + 1 = 5 + 2 = 4 + 3 where 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 are all 7-smooth numbers.
%o A394249 (PARI)
%o A394249 A086299(n)=m=n; forprime(p=2, 7, while(m%p==0, m=m/p)); return(m==1)
%o A394249 A394249(n)=sum(k=1,n/2,A086299(k*(n-k)))
%Y A394249 Cf. A002473, A086299, A397452.
%K A394249 nonn
%O A394249 1,4
